title: DP2Q0950  Poles for 2020 Scythe Snaths (Shafts)
description:
Village Kuznetsovo (Кузнецово), Klin Raion, Moscow Oblast, Russia

The middle two poles are rowan (Sorbus aucuparia), the others are hazel (Corylus avellana). (The middle two poles might also be hazel;  will know when I dig the poles out of the woodshed in spring of 2020.)  Several of these poles terminate in  a 10-15 degree bend.

rowan = mountain ash
label: Original
